e42::a "Loading data into a database, with validation, is slow. Retrieving is much faster." ::e
u43::a Making %notes ::?tc "Notes are more concise than documents, prose, or spoken language. · Notes are condensed intent without flowery elaboration. · AI and LLMs produce fluid %prose language, which is not in note form." ::tip
e44::a "Most graph databases don't give any guidance in modelling or searching. They are based on SQL random access search, but this is not how we need to use graphs." ::e
